m the center of the main halo of\ninterest, higher redshift galaxies have on average higher cold gas content, but\nthe ratio of gas (HI or H$_2$) to star formation rate is similar, indicating\nthat star formation is consistently fed through reservoirs of HI then H$_2$.\nFor a given amount of HI, galaxies have shorter consumption times in more\nmassive halo structures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Nov 2018 15:13:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-08"}
